A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 48-8-3 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 exemptions from sales and use taxes, so as to extend the sunset provision for an exemption
3 from state and local sales and use taxes for the sale or use of certain noncommercial written
4 materials or mailings by certain nonprofit organizations; to provide for related matters; to
5 repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Code Section 48-8-3 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to exemptions from
9 sales and use taxes, is amended by revising paragraph (101) as follows:
10 "(101)(A) The sale or use of noncommercial written materials or mailings by an
11 organization which is exempt from taxation under Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal
12 Revenue Code, if the organization is located in this state and provides such materials
13 to charity supporters for educational, charitable, religious, or fundraising purposes, to
14 the extent provided in subparagraph (B) of this paragraph.
15 (B) This exemption shall apply from July 1, 2018, until July 1, 2026 2031. A
16 qualifying organization must shall pay sales and use tax on all purchases and uses of
